ers with event organizers seeking specialized entertainment acts.', '$500M-$2B', 'high', 'low', 'Event venues, wedding planners, corporate event organizers, and tribute band producers', 3, '["Commission-based marketplace connecting performers with event organizers (15-20% take rate)", "Subscription service for venues providing access to pre-vetted performer networks", "Direct artist management and booking agency specializing in tribute acts"]', NULL, '["Highly fragmented market with numerous competing platforms and local booking agents already established", "Artist licensing and copyright considerations for tribute performances", "Low barriers to entry creating commoditized pricing pressure and margin compression"]', '["Conduct primary research interviews with 15-20 local venues to validate frequency and budget allocation for tribute act bookings", "Map competitive landscape including existing platforms (GigSalad, Thumbtack, local agencies) and identify differentiation opportunities", "Analyze unit economics by modeling typical booking volume, commission rates, and customer acquisition costs in target geography"]', NULL, 'Entertainment venues and event organizers lack efficient mechanisms to source, vet, and book musicians capable of delivering high-quality tribute performances, resulting in time-consuming manual recruitment processes and potential quality inconsistencies.', NULL, 37.3391, -121.9016, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
